{
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>You project a phantasmal image of a creature’s worst fears. Each creature in a 30-foot &amp;Reference[cone]{cone} must succeed on a &amp;Reference[wis]{Wisdom} saving throw or drop whatever it is holding and become &amp;Reference[frightened]{frightened} for the duration.</p>\n<p>While &amp;Reference[frightened]{frightened} by this spell, a creature must take the Dash action and move away from you by the safest available route on each of its turns, unless there is nowhere to move. If the creature ends its turn in a location where it doesn’t have &amp;Reference[line]{line} of sight to you, the creature can make a &amp;Reference[wis]{Wisdom} saving throw. On a successful save, the spell ends for that creature.</p>\n</div>",
